title: How To | Make Eyes Bigger
description:
Try these quick and easy eye makeup steps to make eyes look bigger for a night out. 

Step 1: Apply eyeliner to lower lash line.

Step 2: Double curl your lashes with an eyelash curler. First curl the tips and then the lash line. Which instantly gives you lift.

Step 3: Use two mascaras – One that lengthens and one that volumizes. Gently apply one coat of the lengthening mascara to lower lashes. 

Step 4: Apply 3 coats of the volumizing mascara to upper lashes, wiggling it through the lashes until it reaches the ends. 

Repeat these easy steps as needed to get ready for your night out. Follow our ‘How To’ series for more everyday makeup tips!

asset.author: Neutrogena

transcripts:
[MUSIC PLAYING]

To make your eyes look bigger, grab an eyeliner and apply it to the lower lash line. Double curl your lashes with an eyelash curler. First curl the tips and then the lash line, which instantly gives you lift. Your key step is to work with two mascaras. One that lengthens and one that volumizes. Gently brush one coat of the healthy links mascara along the lower lash line, holding the brush vertically. What I like to do next is add three layers of healthy volume mascara to the upper lashes, wiggling it though the lashes until it reaches the ends. Repeat these easy steps as needed to get ready for your night out.
